description:
The school of hard knocks has just gotten an extreme makeover! When Mokichi arrives at his new school, he makes more than just a little ruckus. Not only does this battle-challenged boy get beaten and thrown around, he is humiliated before the entire school! What's a dude to do? Join the wrestling club! Yuji Shiozaki, creator of the action-packed Battle Vixens, has delivered another knockout, battle-charged manga series that will have reader flipping and flying over the nonstop action.

Back Blurb

The school of hard knocks has just received an extreme make-over! New kid Mokichi wanted nothing more than to become "Big Man on Campus"--and battle-babe Tamako is just the girl to show him how! When Mokichi arrives at his new school, he causes more than just a little ruckus. Not only does this battle-challenged boy get beaten, bloodied and bruised, he is humiliated before the entire school! What's a dude to do? Join the wrestling club!

Round 1 - 9.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Battle Club is back with a hard hitting and wrestle pinning round two. Mokichi and Higushi are slacking in their training. Things heat up when Tamako faces Kuniko in a curry eating contest. When you think it couldn't get any hotter, the girls visit a hotspring. Our band of misfit athletes finally face the 4 Kings of Heaven for an unusual prize.

Back Blurb

Battle Club is back with another hard-hitting round of sweaty action! Mokichi and Higushi are slacking in their training, but things heat up when Tamako faces Kuniko in a curry-eating contest. And just when you think it couldn't get any hotter, the girls visit a hot spring! But the real question in this volume---Who's got the stronger bladder: Tondemon or Taki?

Chapter Titles

  • Round 1
  • Round 2
  • Round 3
  • Round 4
  • Interrelations Chart For Enjoying Battle Club 200% Part 1
  • Interrelations Chart For Enjoying Battle Club 200% Part 2
  • Interrelations Chart For Enjoying Battle Club 200% Part 3: Tamako's Photo Studio Treasures
  • Round 5
  • Round 6
  • Round 7
name: Vol. 2

description:
Tamako and the entire wrestling club are still in the mountains for their summer training camp. Tamako is facing the 2nd Elite Four named Koumoku--a girl who wears a school uniform swimsuit. Tamako's "battle" is to retrieve Koumoku's key from a raging river. Throughout the battle, though, Tamako finds out that Koumoku is searching for her late father's axe in the river...but the weight of the axe is too much, and Koumoku is about to drown!

Back Blurb

Tamako and the entire wrestling club are still in the mountains for their summer training camp, where Tamako faces the Second Elite Four named Koumoku---a girl who wears a school uniform swimsuit.

Tamako's "battle"? She must retrieve Koumoku's key from a roaring river while Koumoku has to deal with some secrets concerning her late father. Clearly these girls have some big issues to get off their chests, but as the white water rages on around the,, can Tamako bury the axe before everyone becomes soaking wet?! Let's hope so... and soon---Mokichi and the wrestling club are about to be introduced to a new nightmare!

Round 1 - 7.

description: Ol’ Skullface sings again! Our charming Mr. Terror – the cursed, undead, rotting, immortal entrepreneur – is back in action! Brutally ripping off his own limbs and “borrowing” other people’s body parts comes in so very handy for the lucrative purposes of assassination, espionage, and other sticky situations. Business is truly recession-proof…but is it plague-proof? Terror better hope so when he agrees to recover a weaponized virus from Middle Eastern terrorists – just one of those odd jobs the unique Mr. Terror is so well suited for. Writer David Lapham (Stray Bullets) brings you another bloody, gruesome, hilarious, ultraviolent adventure in the MAX vein, with jaw-dropping art by Koi Turnbull (Fathom)! Collecting TERROR, INC. - APOCALYPSE SOON #1-4.
name: TPB
The Mad How Not to Do It Book

volume.name: Mad How Not to Do It Book

description:
Raleigh doesn't have a soul. A cat stole it - or at least that's what she tells people - or at least that's what she would tell people if she told people anything. But that would mean talking to people, and the mere thought of social interaction is terrifying. How did such a shy teenage girl end up in a car with three of her hooligan classmates on a cross-country road trip? Being forced to interact with kids her own age is a new and alarming proposition for Raleigh, but maybe it's just what she needs - or maybe it can help her find what she needs - or maybe it can help her to realize that what she needs has been with her all along.

The characters of Lost at Sea would be found in other stories:

  • 2-page full color spread in Oni Press Color Special 2002
  • "Smiling Is Something Other People Do" - Found at radiomaru.com
  • Babyfood - found at radiomaru.com
  • Lost at Sea Strips | 1| 2| 3| 4| 5| - all found on at radiomaru.com
name: Lost at Sea

description:
Spinning out of BATMAN: R.I.P.! With Batman gone, the forces of good and evil in Gotham City struggle for dominance in this new title collecting the five BATMAN: BATTLE FOR THE COWL Specials: ARKHAM ASYLUM, THE NETWORK, MAN-BAT, UNDERGROUND and COMMISSIONER GORDON.

----------

Batman is dead... and Gotham hangs in the balance!

Gotham City lies in chaos and flames - the Batman is dead, and criminals rule the city. But even in her darkest hour, Gotham is not defenseless. As would-be successors battle for the Dark Knight's mantle, there are men and women protecting his city from the trenches.

Unarmed and half-frozen, Commissioner Gordon must stop Mr. Freeze from committing icy mass-murder. Dr. Kirk Langstrom -- Man-Bat -- must overcome the monster within to discover the hero her can be. In the ruins of the asylum that bears his name, Dr. Jeremiah Arkham finds the inspiration to rebuild from his most unusual inmates. Among Gotham's underground, the reformed Riddler pieces together the puzzling new crime boss targeting Penguin and Two-Face. And throughout Gotham, Oracle's network of unlikely heroes may be all that stands between the city and its destruction.

While the Battle for the Cowl rages on, the battle or Gotham is waged! Creators Fabian Nicieza (AZRAEL), Chris Yost (RED ROBIN), David Hine (THE BRAVE AND THE BOLD), Pablo Raimondi (SUPERMAN), Tom Mandrake (THE SPECTRE), Jim Calafiore (GOTHAM UNDERGROUND) and more chronicle the carnage!
name: Battle for the Cowl Companion

volume.name: Batman: Battle for the Cowl Companion

description: Noemie has left her home in France to study abroad. In Onion City there are new friends, new environments, and new loves. There are also new dreams. And not ordinary dreams. Vivid visions of life in a different time and in a different place, but more than that, of a different existence. In Noemie's sleep she's not a woman, but a horse. A noble creature aiding a sick little girl. But how does this effect Noemie's own journey?
name: Gray Horses

description: Salamander Dream is a young girl's journey within a magical forest. As the years pass, she finds herself changing, which in turn, changes her friendship with Salamander. A coming of age story told within innovative layouts and sequential art, Salamander Dream, marks Hope Larson's first full length solo creation within the world of comics.
name: Salamander Dream

description: The epic adventure from SUPERMAN/BATMAN #44-49 by Michael Green and Mike Johnson, two of the writers of the hit TV series Heroes, is now available in trade paperback! The World's Finest team has a new mission: collect all Kryptonite from across the globe — no matter who gets in their way! Includes a foreward by "Dark Knight" co-writer Jonah Nolan!
name: The Search For Kryptonite

description: Abby is back at the same old camp she goes to every summer - except for the fact that this summer, nothing is the same. Her friend Rose is a cabin assistant, her friend Beth is pierced, and now the only person who doesn't seem too cool for Abby is Shasta, the new girl. Shasta, who was struck by lightning, whose Internet boyfriend is a senior in high school, and who is totally annoying to everyone but Abby...
name: Chiggers

description: Heroes are being pulled out of the worlds they know- The Beast. The Witch. Panther. Forge. Polaris. All find themselves in a place out of time with a new mission in life. But something seems to have shifted in the mechanics of the universe, things may not be quite what we remember... But one thing we know for certain- BLINK is BACK! Collecting EXILES #1-6.
